<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-us">
  <head>
    {% include "./head.njk" %}
  </head>
  <body>
    {% include "./header.njk" %}
    <!-- Header-->
    <header class="bg-primary bg-gradient text-white">
        <div class="container px-4 text-center">
            <h1 class="fw-bolder">Welcome to OpenA11y Evaluation Library</h1>
            <p class="lead">Javascript Library for Evaluating WCAG 2.2 Accessibility Requirements.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Main section-->
    <main class="container px-4">
      <div class="row gx-4 justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
          {% block content %}
          <div id="home">
            <h2>Purpose</h2>
            <p>The purpose of the OpenA11y Evaluation libary is to support accessible design for implementation of <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG">W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines</a> level A and AA requirements by creating rules that are based on the following W3C documents:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/">W3C WAI Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.0 (WCAG 2.0).</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/">W3C WAI Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 (WCAG 2.1).</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/">W3C WAI Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.2 (WCAG 2.2).</a></li>

              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria/">W3C WAI Accessible Rich Internet Application (ARIA) specification.</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html-aria/">W3C ARIA in HTML specification.</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/">W3C ARIA Authoring Practices Guide</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/accname-1.2/">W3C Accessible Name and Description Computation</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

            <h2>Open Source</h2>
            <p>The code OpenA11y Evaluation Library is open source and free for anyone to use.  The library is distributed using the <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/MPL/2.0/">Mozilla Public License 2.0</a>.   The source code is available from <a href="https://github.com/opena11y/evaluation-library">OpenA11y Evaluation Library</a> respository.


          {% endblock %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    {% include "./footer.njk" %}
    {% include "./scripts.njk" %}

  </body>
</html>
